  "prompt": "What is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Power County ID?",
  "response": "While I can't provide real-time information or specific recommendations, I can suggest some general steps to find a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Power County, ID:\n\n1. **Online Research**: Use search engines to look for rehab facilities in and near Power County, Idaho. Websites like Psychology Today and SAMHSA (Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration) offer directories of treatment facilities.\n\n2. **Local Health Department**: Contact the Idaho Department of Health and Welfare or local health departments for recommendations on accredited rehab centers.\n\n3. **Consult with Healthcare Providers**: Speak with your primary care physician or a mental health professional for referrals to reputable rehab centers.\n\n4. **Support Groups**: Reach out to local support groups, such as Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) or Narcotics Anonymous (NA), for recommendations from those who have been through treatment.\n\n5. **Insurance Provider**: Check with your health insurance provider to find out which rehab centers are covered under your plan.\n\n6. **Reviews and Testimonials**: Look for testimonials or reviews from former patients to gauge the quality of care and support at different facilities.\n\nBe sure to verify the accreditation and credentials of any facility you consider, and it's helpful to visit the center if possible to ensure it meets your needs.",
